TITLE: Composing and Nesting Styles
DESCRIPTION: This code illustrates how to combine and nest styles using Chalk's chainable API. It shows examples of combining styles, nesting styles of different types, nesting styles of the same type, and using ES2015 template literals for styling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import chalk from 'chalk';

const log = console.log;

// Combine styled and normal strings
log(chalk.blue('Hello') + ' World' + chalk.red('!'));

// Compose multiple styles using the chainable API
log(chalk.blue.bgRed.bold('Hello world!'));

// Pass in multiple arguments
log(chalk.blue('Hello', 'World!', 'Foo', 'bar', 'biz', 'baz'));

// Nest styles
log(chalk.red('Hello', chalk.underline.bgBlue('world') + '!'));

// Nest styles of the same type even (color, underline, background)
log(chalk.green(
	'I am a green line ' +
	chalk.blue.underline.bold('with a blue substring') +
	' that becomes green again!'
));

// ES2015 template literal
log(`
CPU: ${chalk.red('90%')}
RAM: ${chalk.green('40%')}
DISK: ${chalk.yellow('70%')}
`);

// Use RGB colors in terminal emulators that support it.
log(chalk.rgb(123, 45, 67).underline('Underlined reddish color'));
log(chalk.hex('#DEADED').bold('Bold gray!'));
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Defining Custom Themes
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to define custom themes using Chalk by creating reusable style combinations. It defines an `error` style as bold red and a `warning` style using a hex color, then uses them to print messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import chalk from 'chalk';

const error = chalk.bold.red;
const warning = chalk.hex('#FFA500'); // Orange color

console.log(error('Error!'));
console.log(warning('Warning!'));
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic Chalk Usage
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a basic example of using Chalk to colorize a string in the console. It imports the Chalk library and uses the `blue` style to print 'Hello world!' in blue.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import chalk from 'chalk';

console.log(chalk.blue('Hello world!'));
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using String Substitution
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use Chalk with `console.log`'s string substitution feature. It defines a variable `name` and uses Chalk to colorize a greeting message with the variable inserted using `%s`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import chalk from 'chalk';

const name = 'Sindre';
console.log(chalk.green('Hello %s'), name);
//=> 'Hello Sindre'
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating a Custom Chalk Instance
DESCRIPTION: This demonstrates creating a custom Chalk instance with a specific color level. This is useful for controlling color support in reusable modules without affecting global Chalk settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import {Chalk} from 'chalk';

const customChalk = new Chalk({level: 0});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using modifierNames and foregroundColorNames
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to access and use `modifierNames` and `foregroundColorNames` to validate input strings against supported Chalk styles. This helps in scenarios where you need to wrap Chalk functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import {modifierNames, foregroundColorNames} from 'chalk';

console.log(modifierNames.includes('bold'));
//=> true

console.log(foregroundColorNames.includes('pink'));
//=> false
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Chalk via npm
DESCRIPTION: This command demonstrates how to install the Chalk library using npm, a Node.js package manager. This is the first step to using Chalk in a Node.js project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/chalk/chalk/blob/main/readme.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
npm install chalk
```
